\begin_inset Formula $A_{i}\in\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $i\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

, are mutually disjoint, then 
\begin_inset Formula $P\left(\bigcup_{i\in\mathbb{N}}A_{i}\right)=\sum_{i\in\mathbb{N}}P\left(A_{i}\right)$
\end_inset

.
