\begin_layout Itemize
Probability density function (PDF) 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(x\right)=\partial F\left(x\right)/\partial x$
\end_inset

.
 PDF is the Rondom-Nykdin derivative of the probability measure of the random
 variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 with respect to the Lebesgue measure on the real line.
 For a measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 that is absolutely continuous with respect to another measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

, the Rodom-Nykdin derivative is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula $d\lambda/d\mu$
\end_inset

 such that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda\left(A\right)=\int_{A}\frac{d\lambda}{d\mu}d\mu
\]

\end_inset

 for any 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

.
